headline.print_headline: Pennsylvania to Purchase Private Care for Its Poor

docs.abstract: Pennsylvania will become the 27th state to expand Medicaid under the Affordable Care Act, using federal funds to buy private health insurance for about 500,000 low-income residents starting in 2015; Republican Gov Tom Corbett had proposed the plan as an alternative to expanding traditional Medicaid under the health care law, which he opposes.
